WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
- Synced and corrected by <font color="#009BCB"><b>chamallow</b></font> -
- www.addic7ed.com -

2
00:00:05.519 --> 00:00:07.037
In the criminal justice system.

3
00:00:07.104 --> 00:00:08.405
the people are represented

4
00:00:08.505 --> 00:00:10.941
by two separate. yet
equally important groups:

5
00:00:11.008 --> 00:00:12.901
the police. who investigate crime.

6
00:00:13.001 --> 00:00:15.646
and the district attorneys.
who prosecute the offenders.

7
00:00:15.713 --> 00:00:17.598
These are their stories.

8
00:00:19.116 --> 00:00:20.718
Must have had a thousand coffees

9
00:00:20.784 --> 00:00:22.553
while we were waiting to testify.

10
00:00:22.653 --> 00:00:26.457
Maybe we can actually
levitate after this one.

11
00:00:26.490 --> 00:00:29.293
My mom used to drag me to
this stuff when I was a kid.

12
00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:30.644
Oh. yeah?

13
00:00:30.677 --> 00:00:32.863
- Ash Wednesday?
- Mm-hmm.

14
00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:35.799
I'm a proud lapsed
Catholic at this point.

15
00:00:35.833 --> 00:00:38.702
All I really remember is grumpy nuns

16
00:00:38.769 --> 00:00:42.264
and old men wearing
pointy little elf shoes.

17
00:00:42.331 --> 00:00:45.667
And they all smelled like soup.

18
00:00:45.701 --> 00:00:50.380
I'm pretty sure that ash
symbolizes God's mercy.

19
00:00:50.447 --> 00:00:52.683
the promise of a new life.

20
00:00:52.750 --> 00:00:54.276
Is that all?

21
00:00:54.376 --> 00:00:55.444
Is that all?

22
00:00:55.544 --> 00:00:57.254
Look. I get it. It's not for me.

23
00:01:00.282 --> 00:01:02.326
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. Hey.

24
00:01:02.392 --> 00:01:03.619
What's going on? What's going on?

25
00:01:03.685 --> 00:01:04.895
Somebody's shooting!

26
00:01:06.597 --> 00:01:08.724
2-7 Squad. we've got reports of a 10-10

27
00:01:08.791 --> 00:01:10.100
in the Atlas Museum of Art.

28
00:01:10.200 --> 00:01:11.835
Plainclothes detectives responding.

29
00:01:11.902 --> 00:01:13.237
NYPD. Where's the shooter?

30
00:01:13.303 --> 00:01:14.538
- Up at the crown display.
- Where?

31
00:01:14.571 --> 00:01:15.571
- Where?
- The crown!

32
00:01:15.631 --> 00:01:16.774
The crown! Upstairs. second floor!

33
00:01:16.874 --> 00:01:18.242
Second floor. second floor.

34
00:01:21.403 --> 00:01:22.403
Oh. my God.

35
00:01:22.446 --> 00:01:23.580
Hey.

36
00:01:25.382 --> 00:01:28.076
Central. 2-7. 10-10
confirmed. second floor.

37
00:01:28.143 --> 00:01:29.686
Hey. hey. hey. come here.

38
00:01:29.720 --> 00:01:30.720
I got you.

39
00:01:30.754 --> 00:01:31.755
Let me see.

40
00:01:31.822 --> 00:01:33.023
Central. 2-7. We have two GSWs.

41
00:01:33.056 --> 00:01:34.224
This man needs help.

42
00:01:34.291 --> 00:01:35.793
Get us an ambulance.
all available units.

43
00:01:35.893 --> 00:01:37.586
Listen to me. Help is on the way.

44
00:01:37.653 --> 00:01:39.321
Can you tell me who did this to you?

45
00:01:39.388 --> 00:01:41.965
Yes. two... two guys.

46
00:01:42.065 --> 00:01:43.434
They took the crown.

47
00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:46.495
Okay. we got two casings. 9 millimeters.

48
00:01:46.562 --> 00:01:47.805
They went that way.

49
00:01:47.871 --> 00:01:49.039
Okay.

50
00:01:49.072 --> 00:01:50.274
All right. that's great. Hey. hey. hey.

51
00:01:50.374 --> 00:01:51.600
No. no. no. no. no. Listen to me.

52
00:01:51.667 --> 00:01:52.668
Stay with me. Stay with me.

53
00:01:52.768 --> 00:01:53.777
Hey! We're NYPD!

54
00:01:53.877 --> 00:01:55.045
- Come here!
- Oh. my God.

55
00:01:55.112 --> 00:01:56.747
- Hey. Cecil.
- Listen to me.

56
00:01:56.780 --> 00:01:58.282
EMS is on its way. It's
gonna be here any second.

57
00:01:58.348 --> 00:01:59.842
I need you to keep
him up. keep him alert.

58
00:01:59.942 --> 00:02:00.943
and keep pressure on that wound.

59
00:02:01.009 --> 00:02:02.553
You got it? Okay. Come on. let's go.

60
00:02:02.686 --> 00:02:03.946
Hold on. Cecil.

61
00:02:08.826 --> 00:02:10.461
Hey. we're NYPD. Did you see anything?

62
00:02:10.527 --> 00:02:12.454
Two guys with guns. they went that way.

63
00:02:12.521 --> 00:02:13.521
All right. Go to the left.

64
00:02:13.530 --> 00:02:15.424
Get downstairs!

65
00:02:17.701 --> 00:02:19.369
NYPD! Don't move!

66
00:02:22.030 --> 00:02:25.108
10-13. shots fired at the police.

67
00:02:30.305 --> 00:02:31.773
Go. go. go!

68
00:02:38.388 --> 00:02:39.481
Go!

69
00:02:47.631 --> 00:02:49.500
Hey! Police! Stop!

70
00:02:51.560 --> 00:02:52.769
Cover me.

71
00:02:52.803 --> 00:02:54.288
Hey! NYPD!

72
00:02:54.321 --> 00:02:55.672
Stop!

73
00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:03.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

74
00:03:04.481 --> 00:03:07.351
Back entrance. Back entrance.

75
00:03:12.122 --> 00:03:14.024
Get out of here!

76
00:03:14.124 --> 00:03:15.984
- Go left!
- 2-7 Squad to Central.

77
00:03:16.018 --> 00:03:17.461
I'm on foot pursuit with the other perp.

78
00:03:17.528 --> 00:03:19.446
headed to the back parking lot!

79
00:03:21.365 --> 00:03:23.233
Central. 2-7. I'm pursuing on foot!

80
00:03:23.300 --> 00:03:24.701
Perp is on a bike!

81
00:03:28.171 --> 00:03:30.874
He's heading eastbound.
exiting the parking lot.

82
00:03:30.941 --> 00:03:32.292
Damn it.

83
00:03:34.369 --> 00:03:35.979
NYPD! Stop!

84
00:03:36.113 --> 00:03:37.773
Hold it!

85
00:03:40.217 --> 00:03:41.652
Stop right there!

86
00:03:41.685 --> 00:03:43.153
Drop your weapon right now!

87
00:03:43.186 --> 00:03:45.489
Drop your weapon and get on the ground.

88
00:03:45.556 --> 00:03:47.641
Drop your weapon now!

89
00:03:48.825 --> 00:03:50.594
- Drop that weapon!
- Put it down!

90
00:03:50.694 --> 00:03:51.887
Drop it!

91
00:03:51.954 --> 00:03:53.522
Everybody. take a breath!

92
00:03:57.893 --> 00:03:59.736
Hey!

93
00:03:59.803 --> 00:04:00.963
Come on. man. it's not worth it.

94
00:04:01.063 --> 00:04:02.906
Don't do this.

95
00:04:08.478 --> 00:04:10.539
Suspect down.

96
00:04:11.907 --> 00:04:14.476
2-7 Squad to Central. get us a bus now.

97
00:04:14.576 --> 00:04:18.255
Multiple gunshots. but
the police are not injured.

98
00:05:18.281 --> 00:05:19.983
How's the wounded security guard?

99
00:05:20.050 --> 00:05:21.752
Didn't make it.

100
00:05:21.785 --> 00:05:23.153
What happened here?

101
00:05:23.220 --> 00:05:24.755
Guy drew down a patrol officer.

102
00:05:24.788 --> 00:05:26.715
It was a good shoot.

103
00:05:26.815 --> 00:05:28.692
.40-cal Smith & Wesson.

104
00:05:28.759 --> 00:05:31.319
but the cases up in the
Crown Room were 9-millimeter.

105
00:05:31.386 --> 00:05:34.531
So that's not the murder weapon.

106
00:05:34.631 --> 00:05:37.300
That's kind of a funky tattoo.

107
00:05:37.367 --> 00:05:39.269
Let's see if it's in the database.

108
00:05:39.302 --> 00:05:40.937
Anything on the body?

109
00:05:41.004 --> 00:05:42.664
No cell and no wallet.

110
00:05:42.731 --> 00:05:45.842
But he was wearing an
official-looking art museum ID.

111
00:05:45.909 --> 00:05:49.304
and he had a legit
security guard uniform.

112
00:05:49.337 --> 00:05:50.981
You think these guys really worked here.

113
00:05:51.014 --> 00:05:53.116
or was it an inside job?

114
00:05:53.183 --> 00:05:54.434
We'll see.

115
00:05:56.620 --> 00:05:58.822
We got units looking for your guy...

116
00:05:58.889 --> 00:06:01.625
BOLO. grid search.
choke points. all of it.

117
00:06:01.725 --> 00:06:03.393
So far. nothing.

118
00:06:03.460 --> 00:06:05.921
The victim's name is Cecil Carbo.

119
00:06:06.021 --> 00:06:07.798
Apparently he's a bit of
an institution around here.

120
00:06:07.864 --> 00:06:10.358
Been here forever. Everybody loved him.

121
00:06:10.425 --> 00:06:13.136
Eyewitnesses who fled the
scene said that the thieves

122
00:06:13.170 --> 00:06:15.372
gained access to this
room by clearing it out.

123
00:06:15.439 --> 00:06:17.699
saying that there was some sort
of event that was gonna happen

124
00:06:17.766 --> 00:06:18.975
in this part of the museum.

125
00:06:19.076 --> 00:06:21.945
So basically. the thieves didn't have

126
00:06:22.045 --> 00:06:23.997
to lift a finger to clear this place out

127
00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:25.482
until Mr. Carbo stepped
in and stopped them?

128
00:06:25.615 --> 00:06:26.883
Looks that way.

129
00:06:26.983 --> 00:06:28.518
At least there's a lot
of cameras here. though.

130
00:06:28.552 --> 00:06:29.778
- Should be helpful.
- And what is this?

131
00:06:29.878 --> 00:06:31.154
What was this?

132
00:06:31.188 --> 00:06:32.681
Crown of Popayán?

133
00:06:32.714 --> 00:06:34.024
I don't know.

134
00:06:34.091 --> 00:06:35.684
- 16th century or something?
- Oh. my God!

135
00:06:35.717 --> 00:06:36.827
- Cecil! Cecil!
- Ma'am. Ma'am!

136
00:06:36.927 --> 00:06:38.095
How'd they get in here?

137
00:06:38.161 --> 00:06:39.296
He's my husband!

138
00:06:39.362 --> 00:06:40.430
That's how they got in here.

139
00:06:40.497 --> 00:06:42.399
He's my husband!

140
00:06:42.466 --> 00:06:44.234
Cardinal Keane.

141
00:06:45.736 --> 00:06:48.964
This is Mr. Carbo's wife. Valentina.

142
00:06:49.064 --> 00:06:51.299
and their daughter. Luna.

143
00:06:51.399 --> 00:06:52.476
I'm Lieutenant Brady.

144
00:06:52.576 --> 00:06:53.735
This is Detective Riley.

145
00:06:53.802 --> 00:06:55.412
Very sorry for your loss.

146
00:06:55.479 --> 00:06:57.314
I saw them downstairs. and
I thought they should have

147
00:06:57.380 --> 00:06:59.182
an opportunity to say goodbye.

148
00:06:59.216 --> 00:07:01.952
Respectfully. this is
an active crime scene.

149
00:07:02.052 --> 00:07:04.154
Mr. Carbo was a man of deep faith.

150
00:07:04.221 --> 00:07:05.455
a son of the church.

151
00:07:05.522 --> 00:07:07.457
He requested to guard the crown.

152
00:07:07.524 --> 00:07:09.526
He said it was a privilege.

153
00:07:09.593 --> 00:07:12.796
It is Ash Wednesday. and
I'd like to administer

154
00:07:12.863 --> 00:07:14.498
the prayer for the deceased.

155
00:07:14.598 --> 00:07:17.267
Your Eminence. this is a crime scene...

156
00:07:17.334 --> 00:07:19.102
my crime scene.

157
00:07:19.169 --> 00:07:21.505
Which means we need to
preserve it exactly as it is.

158
00:07:21.605 --> 00:07:23.765
That's the only way we're
gonna catch these guys.

159
00:07:23.832 --> 00:07:27.569
This man just died in
service of the church.

160
00:07:27.602 --> 00:07:30.547
And to deny him the
prayer for the deceased

161
00:07:30.580 --> 00:07:32.716
would be a crime unto itself.

162
00:07:32.749 --> 00:07:35.786
Well. I'm afraid that's
beyond our jurisdiction.

163
00:07:40.524 --> 00:07:43.660
It seems this room is
sacred ground to all of us.

164
00:07:43.727 --> 00:07:46.396
just for different reasons.

165
00:07:46.429 --> 00:07:49.416
I'm not asking you to do this for me.

166
00:07:49.449 --> 00:07:51.626
Do it for them.

167
00:07:56.798 --> 00:07:58.308
Don't touch anything.

168
00:08:12.489 --> 00:08:14.591
You have loved the church here on Earth.

169
00:08:14.624 --> 00:08:17.561
Now. rejoice in her glory in heaven.

170
00:08:17.661 --> 00:08:21.097
Into your hands. merciful Father.

171
00:08:21.164 --> 00:08:23.366
we commend your servant.

172
00:08:23.466 --> 00:08:26.036
Acknowledge him as one of your own.

173
00:08:26.136 --> 00:08:28.205
May the angels lead you to paradise.

174
00:08:28.271 --> 00:08:31.875
In the name of the Father.
the Son. and the Holy Ghost.

175
00:08:42.052 --> 00:08:43.912
So we found this on one of the thieves.

176
00:08:44.012 --> 00:08:44.920
Is that real?

177
00:08:44.921 --> 00:08:46.056
Did he work here?

178
00:08:46.156 --> 00:08:47.457
I don't recognize the face.

179
00:08:47.557 --> 00:08:50.610
And there's no employee
here named James Sullivan.

180
00:08:52.345 --> 00:08:54.931
But yes. that's a real ID.

181
00:08:55.031 --> 00:08:58.735
It was swiped to enter the
facility at 10:43 this morning.

182
00:08:58.802 --> 00:09:01.037
Six minutes before the shooting.

183
00:09:01.104 --> 00:09:02.472
Okay. obviously we gotta go through

184
00:09:02.572 --> 00:09:04.241
all of your CCTV footage.

185
00:09:04.307 --> 00:09:05.500
There isn't any.

186
00:09:07.702 --> 00:09:09.212
How is that possible?

187
00:09:09.312 --> 00:09:11.615
Our system was rebooting
during the robbery.

188
00:09:11.715 --> 00:09:13.667
The feeds went offline for 12 minutes.

189
00:09:13.700 --> 00:09:15.502
Well. that's convenient.

190
00:09:15.535 --> 00:09:17.879
We'll look into it
right away. obviously.

191
00:09:17.946 --> 00:09:19.381
Okay.

192
00:09:19.447 --> 00:09:20.849
what can you tell us about the crown?

193
00:09:20.882 --> 00:09:22.550
Why would someone wanna steal that

194
00:09:22.617 --> 00:09:24.261
and not take anything else?

195
00:09:24.361 --> 00:09:28.790
Well. that's nearly 5 pounds
of the purest gold I know.

196
00:09:28.890 --> 00:09:31.334
450 emeralds.

197
00:09:31.368 --> 00:09:36.072
This one. the Illapu. is worth
$15 million. give or take.

198
00:09:36.139 --> 00:09:37.274
Yowza.

199
00:09:37.374 --> 00:09:38.675
That's not the only reason.

200
00:09:38.708 --> 00:09:40.568
Indigenous Colombians believe

201
00:09:40.635 --> 00:09:43.013
that the crown belongs to
them. not the Catholic Church.

202
00:09:43.046 --> 00:09:45.282
So they think the Catholics
stole the crown from them.

203
00:09:45.348 --> 00:09:46.483
Yeah.

204
00:09:46.549 --> 00:09:47.918
In the 16th century.

205
00:09:47.984 --> 00:09:51.413
2 million people in South
America died of smallpox.

206
00:09:51.479 --> 00:09:54.249
But the little village
of Popayán was spared.

207
00:09:54.316 --> 00:09:56.718
So the Colombians think
there was some sort

208
00:09:56.751 --> 00:09:58.194
of divine intervention?

209
00:09:58.261 --> 00:09:59.596
Precisely.

210
00:09:59.663 --> 00:10:01.756
They've been trying to
reclaim it for years in court.

211
00:10:01.823 --> 00:10:03.633
but the lawsuits never went anywhere.

212
00:10:03.733 --> 00:10:05.368
And how did it end up here?

213
00:10:05.468 --> 00:10:07.370
We got the crown a couple of months ago

214
00:10:07.470 --> 00:10:09.773
on loan from the Vatican.

215
00:10:09.839 --> 00:10:13.443
It's been a wildly
popular exhibit for us.

216
00:10:13.510 --> 00:10:16.671
There was this Colombian.
this rabble rouser

217
00:10:16.738 --> 00:10:18.782
named Amaru Yupanqui.

218
00:10:18.848 --> 00:10:20.884
He filed a new lawsuit
against the museum.

219
00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:22.285
When that was dismissed.

220
00:10:22.352 --> 00:10:25.113
he went so far as to threaten me.

221
00:10:25.180 --> 00:10:26.181
When?

222
00:10:26.247 --> 00:10:27.991
Last week.

223
00:10:28.058 --> 00:10:30.760
He sent me an email saying
that if I didn't cooperate.

224
00:10:30.794 --> 00:10:34.798
he would take the crown
by any means necessary.

225
00:10:40.537 --> 00:10:42.964
I was blowing off steam.

226
00:10:43.031 --> 00:10:45.742
Some people go for a run.

227
00:10:45.809 --> 00:10:47.944
You write death threats?

228
00:10:47.978 --> 00:10:50.246
I believe that Indigenous Colombians are

229
00:10:50.380 --> 00:10:52.807
the rightful owners of
the Crown of Popayán.

230
00:10:52.874 --> 00:10:54.751
I am passionate about that.

231
00:10:54.784 --> 00:10:56.619
and I will never stop fighting for it.

232
00:10:56.686 --> 00:10:58.088
but I didn't kill anyone.

233
00:10:58.154 --> 00:11:00.089
Well. that doesn't mean
this whole thing wasn't

234
00:11:00.156 --> 00:11:01.624
your idea in the first place.

235
00:11:01.658 --> 00:11:03.526
I mean. maybe you hired those
two guys to steal the crown.

236
00:11:03.593 --> 00:11:04.986
Please.

237
00:11:05.053 --> 00:11:06.329
Where were you this
morning around 10:30?

238
00:11:06.429 --> 00:11:07.781
- At mass.
- What church?

239
00:11:07.814 --> 00:11:09.657
St. Augustine's on Benton Avenue.

240
00:11:09.724 --> 00:11:11.059
What were you praying for?

241
00:11:11.159 --> 00:11:12.460
Their success?

242
00:11:14.304 --> 00:11:17.207
Remember that you are dust.

243
00:11:17.307 --> 00:11:20.977
and to dust you shall return.

244
00:11:21.010 --> 00:11:23.797
I was praying that I might live wisely

245
00:11:23.830 --> 00:11:25.515
with whatever time I have.

246
00:11:25.582 --> 00:11:28.243
which would not include
hiring two imbeciles to steal

247
00:11:28.309 --> 00:11:31.179
something from a museum.

248
00:11:31.246 --> 00:11:33.990
Let me ask you something.

249
00:11:34.057 --> 00:11:37.152
You've been pissed at
the church for years.

250
00:11:37.185 --> 00:11:38.962
but you still go to mass?

251
00:11:39.028 --> 00:11:40.663
You're still a believer?

252
00:11:40.730 --> 00:11:43.133
You're confusing the church with faith.

253
00:11:43.166 --> 00:11:45.485
which is exactly what the church wants.

254
00:11:45.518 --> 00:11:47.429
That's how we got into this mess.

255
00:11:47.529 --> 00:11:48.805
How's that?

256
00:11:48.838 --> 00:11:52.142
Indigenous artisans spent
six years making the crown.

257
00:11:52.275 --> 00:11:56.913
For 400 years. we worshipped
it as an emblem of faith itself.

258
00:11:57.013 --> 00:11:59.816
And then the church. as you call it.

259
00:11:59.849 --> 00:12:03.511
suddenly decided that
poor Colombians are not

260
00:12:03.545 --> 00:12:06.623
sophisticated enough to
be guardians of the crown.

261
00:12:06.723 --> 00:12:09.025
They snatched it. took it away.

262
00:12:09.092 --> 00:12:12.796
People like me. people of faith.

263
00:12:12.896 --> 00:12:16.933
I am seeking a union with God...

264
00:12:17.033 --> 00:12:19.502
truth. moral order.

265
00:12:19.536 --> 00:12:22.864
The church is only
interested in market share.

266
00:12:22.897 --> 00:12:24.991
protecting their brand.

267
00:12:27.235 --> 00:12:30.163
We don't get many people
in here as cynical as me.

268
00:12:32.382 --> 00:12:33.867
Can I go home now?

269
00:12:33.900 --> 00:12:35.718
Yes.

270
00:12:35.785 --> 00:12:38.555
We're gonna confirm you
were at mass this morning.

271
00:12:38.588 --> 00:12:40.006
Please do.

272
00:12:44.919 --> 00:12:47.388
Uh. you guys remember Lieutenant Brady?

273
00:12:47.422 --> 00:12:48.756
Your Eminence?

274
00:12:48.823 --> 00:12:51.401
The Archbishop was looking
for an update on the case.

275
00:12:51.434 --> 00:12:54.404
Mrs. Carbo's husband gave
his life protecting the crown.

276
00:12:54.437 --> 00:12:57.507
which means he gave his life
protecting the church itself.

277
00:12:57.574 --> 00:12:59.609
Nothing's more important
to our community

278
00:12:59.709 --> 00:13:01.711
than getting justice for
him. for his family...

279
00:13:01.845 --> 00:13:02.904
nothing.

280
00:13:02.937 --> 00:13:04.614
We understand.

281
00:13:04.681 --> 00:13:07.909
I appreciate your
concern. but I assure you.

282
00:13:07.942 --> 00:13:11.154
we're using all of
our resources on this.

283
00:13:11.221 --> 00:13:14.290
But so far. the only
suspect they have is me.

284
00:13:14.390 --> 00:13:15.692
You know who I am?

285
00:13:15.792 --> 00:13:17.393
Should I?

286
00:13:17.427 --> 00:13:19.128
I'm glad the crown is gone.

287
00:13:19.195 --> 00:13:22.332
And I hope you never get it back.

288
00:13:22.432 --> 00:13:25.969
I couldn't care less about the crown.

289
00:13:26.035 --> 00:13:27.770
Right.

290
00:13:27.837 --> 00:13:30.640
You know. a good man was just murdered.

291
00:13:32.275 --> 00:13:35.345
I'm very sorry for your loss. ma'am.

292
00:13:42.485 --> 00:13:45.688
Hey. Amaru Yupanqui was
at St. Augustine's Church

293
00:13:45.788 --> 00:13:47.257
at the time of the
shooting. just like he said.

294
00:13:47.290 --> 00:13:48.758
Yeah. He didn't feel right for it.

295
00:13:48.791 --> 00:13:50.426
but the guy was definitely intense.

296
00:13:50.560 --> 00:13:52.095
Yeah. we'll keep an eye on him.

297
00:13:52.128 --> 00:13:53.763
Where are we with everything else?

298
00:13:53.830 --> 00:13:56.599
I ran our dead thief's tattoo
through the gang database.

299
00:13:56.733 --> 00:13:57.967
No hits.

300
00:13:58.034 --> 00:13:59.969
So I did a reverse image search.

301
00:14:00.036 --> 00:14:05.333
Turns out it's a military
thing used by this unit.

302
00:14:06.776 --> 00:14:09.345
Special Operations
Reconnaissance Detachment.

303
00:14:09.412 --> 00:14:11.948
Yeah. elite troops...
behind enemy lines.

304
00:14:12.048 --> 00:14:13.783
high-value targets. that kind of thing.

305
00:14:13.883 --> 00:14:16.452
Pentagon keeps a DNA
database of personnel to use

306
00:14:16.486 --> 00:14:18.188
in case they got to identify remains.

307
00:14:18.288 --> 00:14:20.640
We sent them a sample
from our deceased thief.

308
00:14:20.673 --> 00:14:22.525
and we got a hit.

309
00:14:22.592 --> 00:14:27.163
Frank Henry Stephens.
Three tours in Afghanistan.

310
00:14:27.230 --> 00:14:28.464
Did you get an address?

311
00:14:28.498 --> 00:14:29.799
Astoria.

312
00:14:29.866 --> 00:14:30.984
Landlord said that Frank Stephens lived

313
00:14:31.017 --> 00:14:32.360
there with his girlfriend.

314
00:14:32.427 --> 00:14:33.570
Well. great. Go.

315
00:14:33.670 --> 00:14:35.330
- Yeah.
- Okay.

316
00:14:37.432 --> 00:14:38.908
This can't be happening.

317
00:14:38.975 --> 00:14:40.510
I know this is a lot
to process right now.

318
00:14:40.543 --> 00:14:42.879
Ms. Campbell. but you need to
tell us everything you know.

319
00:14:42.979 --> 00:14:44.664
and you need to tell us right now!

320
00:14:44.697 --> 00:14:46.182
There's nothing to tell!

321
00:14:46.249 --> 00:14:48.151
Frank would never do
something like this.

322
00:14:48.284 --> 00:14:49.669
He's not a thief.

323
00:14:49.702 --> 00:14:51.212
He's sure as hell ain't a murderer.

324
00:14:51.279 --> 00:14:52.947
- Going somewhere?
- It's Frank's.

325
00:14:53.047 --> 00:14:54.282
He had a business trip.

326
00:14:54.382 --> 00:14:55.959
What business is that exactly?

327
00:14:56.059 --> 00:14:57.060
Well. I'm not sure.

328
00:14:57.160 --> 00:14:58.561
- You're not sure?
- No.

329
00:14:58.628 --> 00:15:00.063
She's not sure what her
boyfriend did for a living.

330
00:15:00.163 --> 00:15:01.664
That's cute.

331
00:15:01.698 --> 00:15:03.900
Because we happen to know
that your boyfriend reported

332
00:15:03.967 --> 00:15:06.869
no income and filed
no taxes since he was

333
00:15:06.903 --> 00:15:09.130
dishonorably discharged back in 2021.

334
00:15:09.230 --> 00:15:10.940
Look. you're not gonna wanna hear this.

335
00:15:11.040 --> 00:15:13.610
but Frank was never
coming back after that trip

336
00:15:13.676 --> 00:15:17.513
because he chose the
crown. money over you.

337
00:15:17.580 --> 00:15:19.198
He's dead.

338
00:15:19.232 --> 00:15:21.576
So there's no need for you
to cover for him anymore.

339
00:15:21.643 --> 00:15:22.852
I'm not covering for him.

340
00:15:22.919 --> 00:15:24.354
I don't know anything. I swear.

341
00:15:24.420 --> 00:15:26.322
Look. Look at this.

342
00:15:26.422 --> 00:15:28.324
That's who Frank did this with.

343
00:15:28.424 --> 00:15:30.026
Who is that?

344
00:15:30.159 --> 00:15:31.552
I don't know.

345
00:15:33.062 --> 00:15:34.430
Was Frank having any money trouble?

346
00:15:34.530 --> 00:15:36.666
- Anybody threaten him lately?
- No.

347
00:15:36.766 --> 00:15:38.534
Anyone unusual come to
the apartment recently?

348
00:15:38.668 --> 00:15:40.103
No.

349
00:15:40.169 --> 00:15:42.905
I mean. Frank's buddy
came by last night.

350
00:15:42.972 --> 00:15:44.766
but that's not weird. He's
over here all the time.

351
00:15:44.832 --> 00:15:46.743
Tell me about this buddy.

352
00:15:46.776 --> 00:15:48.411
He's just some guy.

353
00:15:48.478 --> 00:15:49.837
He lives here in Astoria.

354
00:15:49.937 --> 00:15:51.347
He...

355
00:15:53.516 --> 00:15:55.952
He what. Amy?

356
00:15:56.019 --> 00:15:58.788
I think he works at the museum.

357
00:16:00.923 --> 00:16:02.358
What is going on?

358
00:16:02.425 --> 00:16:04.193
Why'd you bring me down here?

359
00:16:04.294 --> 00:16:05.995
- Really. Joe? Come on.
- Yes. really.

360
00:16:06.095 --> 00:16:07.789
- I... I didn't do anything wrong.
- Oh.

361
00:16:07.855 --> 00:16:09.265
Well. then you should
just sit back and relax.

362
00:16:09.332 --> 00:16:12.101
and I'll just lay out all
the ways you're screwed.

363
00:16:12.135 --> 00:16:15.805
This is the museum security system log.

364
00:16:15.872 --> 00:16:18.107
A security guard named
Danny Gardner logged

365
00:16:18.174 --> 00:16:22.645
into the system at 10:24 a.m.
to order a reboot of the CCTV.

366
00:16:22.712 --> 00:16:24.213
This is what allowed the thieves

367
00:16:24.280 --> 00:16:25.481
12 minutes to get in and out.

368
00:16:25.548 --> 00:16:27.141
So you should go talk to Danny.

369
00:16:27.208 --> 00:16:28.810
We did.

370
00:16:28.876 --> 00:16:31.254
Turns out Danny called
in sick this morning.

371
00:16:31.320 --> 00:16:32.689
He wasn't at the museum.

372
00:16:32.755 --> 00:16:34.190
You were.

373
00:16:34.290 --> 00:16:37.226
And Danny told us that a few days ago.

374
00:16:37.326 --> 00:16:39.595
you asked him for his login credentials

375
00:16:39.629 --> 00:16:41.764
because yours weren't working.

376
00:16:41.798 --> 00:16:44.100
Danny didn't order the reboot.

377
00:16:44.233 --> 00:16:46.102
You did.

378
00:16:46.169 --> 00:16:48.237
Oh. wait. there is more.

379
00:16:48.338 --> 00:16:52.166
You reported your ID missing
twice in the past three weeks.

380
00:16:52.233 --> 00:16:55.178
And the funny thing is. the
IDs that the thieves used

381
00:16:55.244 --> 00:16:57.572
to gain access to the
museum just so happened

382
00:16:57.638 --> 00:16:59.482
to be your lost ones.

383
00:16:59.549 --> 00:17:01.350
with an assist from
Photoshop. of course.

384
00:17:03.720 --> 00:17:05.304
I wasn't the one who stole that thing.

385
00:17:05.338 --> 00:17:06.806
and I didn't hurt anybody.

386
00:17:06.839 --> 00:17:08.683
Unfortunately for you.
that doesn't matter.

387
00:17:08.750 --> 00:17:10.693
because unless you talk. chances are

388
00:17:10.793 --> 00:17:12.595
you're the only sucker going
down for this whole thing.

389
00:17:12.695 --> 00:17:13.996
And that means we are gonna come at you

390
00:17:14.063 --> 00:17:15.364
with everything we got.

391
00:17:15.431 --> 00:17:17.425
You will never eat
Mommy's meatloaf again.

392
00:17:17.525 --> 00:17:19.135
She's dead.

393
00:17:19.202 --> 00:17:20.928
She was a lousy cook.

394
00:17:21.028 --> 00:17:22.538
So was mine.

395
00:17:27.435 --> 00:17:29.979
Okay.

396
00:17:30.046 --> 00:17:32.248
Okay. but I want a deal.

397
00:17:32.348 --> 00:17:35.042
I'm not saying a damn
thing until that's done.

398
00:17:53.603 --> 00:17:55.071
Queen for a Day?

399
00:17:55.204 --> 00:17:56.522
What the hell does that even...

400
00:17:56.556 --> 00:17:57.940
Yeah. it's a funny name.

401
00:17:58.007 --> 00:18:00.209
It's actually named
after an old game show.

402
00:18:00.343 --> 00:18:02.904
It means you tell us what you know.

403
00:18:03.037 --> 00:18:05.214
we can't use that
information against you.

404
00:18:05.248 --> 00:18:07.250
This is what you wanted. Joe.

405
00:18:08.918 --> 00:18:11.020
You don't do this. you're
looking at felony murder.

406
00:18:11.120 --> 00:18:12.355
You want reduced charges?

407
00:18:12.388 --> 00:18:13.681
This is what that looks like.

408
00:18:13.748 --> 00:18:15.057
You tell the truth today.

409
00:18:15.091 --> 00:18:16.509
You testify at trial.

410
00:18:19.295 --> 00:18:20.463
Yeah. okay.

411
00:18:20.530 --> 00:18:21.714
Good.

412
00:18:21.747 --> 00:18:24.500
Our primary concern
right now is identifying

413
00:18:24.567 --> 00:18:26.936
and capturing the thief
that's still at large.

414
00:18:27.003 --> 00:18:28.371
What is his name?

415
00:18:28.404 --> 00:18:30.006
He goes by Flaco.

416
00:18:30.039 --> 00:18:32.241
- No. what is his real name?
- I don't know.

417
00:18:32.341 --> 00:18:33.676
That's what everybody calls him.

418
00:18:33.709 --> 00:18:35.394
I only met him once. a few weeks ago.

419
00:18:35.428 --> 00:18:36.437
Where?

420
00:18:36.571 --> 00:18:38.548
Some bar in Queens.

421
00:18:38.648 --> 00:18:40.274
I don't know.

422
00:18:40.374 --> 00:18:42.735
Frank... Frank drove.

423
00:18:42.768 --> 00:18:43.886
Frank would know.

424
00:18:43.953 --> 00:18:45.713
Frank is dead. Joe.

425
00:18:45.780 --> 00:18:47.690
Yeah. he's dead because
you people shot him. lady!

426
00:18:47.757 --> 00:18:49.659
Lady. Do they call you Lady?

427
00:18:49.725 --> 00:18:50.793
That guy was like a brother to me!

428
00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:52.628
Joe.

429
00:18:57.867 --> 00:19:00.228
Flaco.

430
00:19:00.294 --> 00:19:01.404
I don't know.

431
00:19:01.437 --> 00:19:02.872
He's a Spanish dude.

432
00:19:02.939 --> 00:19:05.299
From Spain or. like. Latin?

433
00:19:05.433 --> 00:19:06.909
Puerto Rican? Dominican?

434
00:19:07.009 --> 00:19:08.970
Yeah. that.

435
00:19:09.103 --> 00:19:11.247
What else you know about him?

436
00:19:11.314 --> 00:19:13.482
He's about my age. my height.

437
00:19:15.117 --> 00:19:18.437
But Joe. if they find
this man. arrest him.

438
00:19:18.471 --> 00:19:20.556
if you saw him in court.
you'd recognize him.

439
00:19:20.623 --> 00:19:22.225
You could point him out to the jury

440
00:19:22.291 --> 00:19:25.595
and say. yeah. that's the guy.

441
00:19:25.695 --> 00:19:28.164
Yeah. sure.

442
00:19:28.264 --> 00:19:30.992
Sure. So your friend.

443
00:19:31.125 --> 00:19:33.202
Frank Stephens. how did
he know this Flaco guy?

444
00:19:33.269 --> 00:19:34.470
How did they meet?

445
00:19:34.504 --> 00:19:36.706
They served together in Afghanistan.

446
00:19:36.772 --> 00:19:38.174
And the robbery?

447
00:19:38.307 --> 00:19:39.775
How'd they plan it and coordinate it?

448
00:19:39.876 --> 00:19:41.410
Used WhatsApp?

449
00:19:41.477 --> 00:19:43.838
Signal maybe. so the
messages were encrypted?

450
00:19:43.938 --> 00:19:45.214
They used pagers.

451
00:19:45.281 --> 00:19:46.807
Pagers?

452
00:19:46.841 --> 00:19:49.977
Like it's 1995 and
Coolio's on the radio?

453
00:19:51.687 --> 00:19:54.357
Where do you even get a pager anymore?

454
00:19:57.193 --> 00:19:58.761
Yeah. Here it is.

455
00:19:58.828 --> 00:20:00.496
We issued two pagers to Frank Stephens

456
00:20:00.530 --> 00:20:01.664
a couple months back.

457
00:20:01.697 --> 00:20:03.366
What's the second name on the account?

458
00:20:03.466 --> 00:20:04.525
There isn't one.

459
00:20:04.625 --> 00:20:06.193
Why not?

460
00:20:06.294 --> 00:20:08.487
Pagers. they ain't like cell phones.

461
00:20:08.521 --> 00:20:10.239
If this guy. Frank
Stephens. comes in here

462
00:20:10.306 --> 00:20:12.174
and wants to rent two pagers.
we give him two pagers.

463
00:20:12.275 --> 00:20:13.709
Once he walks out the
door. he can give them

464
00:20:13.843 --> 00:20:15.378
to whoever the hell he wants.

465
00:20:18.030 --> 00:20:19.682
The system does keep track

466
00:20:19.782 --> 00:20:22.009
of the last 20 messages
sent by each pager.

467
00:20:22.043 --> 00:20:24.845
So I know it's not a lot.

468
00:20:24.879 --> 00:20:26.422
Well. that should be plenty. Thank you.

469
00:20:26.489 --> 00:20:27.790
Yeah.

470
00:20:27.857 --> 00:20:29.884
Morse code? Is that still a thing?

471
00:20:30.017 --> 00:20:31.894
Yeah. special ops forces
are still trained in it.

472
00:20:32.028 --> 00:20:33.729
- And you know it?
- Nope.

473
00:20:33.796 --> 00:20:35.331
But there's an app for it.

474
00:20:35.398 --> 00:20:37.224
Hey. check this out.

475
00:20:37.358 --> 00:20:39.402
Flight 289.

476
00:20:40.636 --> 00:20:42.171
What airline?

477
00:20:42.204 --> 00:20:46.167
Looks like Pathways
Airlines has a Flight 289.

478
00:20:46.233 --> 00:20:48.344
Flies JFK to Miami
every day at 3:00 p.m.

479
00:20:48.377 --> 00:20:49.879
And the message says.
"We're leaving tomorrow."

480
00:20:49.979 --> 00:20:51.213
but that's actually today.

481
00:20:51.280 --> 00:20:52.840
Okay. I'll pull up the flight manifest.

482
00:20:52.907 --> 00:20:55.151
cross-check it with the
list of soldiers who served

483
00:20:55.217 --> 00:20:56.586
with Stephens in Afghanistan.

484
00:20:56.719 --> 00:20:58.537
If we get a hit. that's our killer.

485
00:20:58.571 --> 00:20:59.855
Plane leaves in an hour.

486
00:20:59.889 --> 00:21:00.915
Get going.

487
00:21:02.725 --> 00:21:06.195
This is the final call for
Flight 289 with service to Miami.

488
00:21:06.295 --> 00:21:07.863
All remaining passengers proceed

489
00:21:07.930 --> 00:21:10.533
immediately to Gate C22.

490
00:21:10.566 --> 00:21:12.902
Where the hell is this guy?

491
00:21:18.399 --> 00:21:20.142
Oh. the overhead bin is full.

492
00:21:20.209 --> 00:21:22.194
We'll need to gate-check your bag.

493
00:21:23.813 --> 00:21:25.940
That's weird.

494
00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:27.283
Last name?

495
00:21:27.416 --> 00:21:28.551
Salazar.

496
00:21:28.651 --> 00:21:30.219
Luis Salazar.

497
00:21:30.319 --> 00:21:32.254
Flight's full. Flaco.

498
00:21:32.355 --> 00:21:33.889
So where is it?

499
00:21:33.990 --> 00:21:35.257
Where's the crown. huh?

500
00:21:35.358 --> 00:21:37.785
No idea what you're talking about. man.

501
00:21:43.699 --> 00:21:45.134
Vince!

502
00:21:47.203 --> 00:21:49.238
Pager.

503
00:21:49.338 --> 00:21:51.107
Turn around.

504
00:21:51.240 --> 00:21:53.709
Luis Salazar. you're under arrest

505
00:21:53.776 --> 00:21:55.778
for the murder of Cecil Carbo.

506
00:22:06.055 --> 00:22:09.225
We have a suspect in
custody named Luis Salazar.

507
00:22:09.291 --> 00:22:10.893
He's a former special ops guy.

508
00:22:10.926 --> 00:22:12.995
We caught him as he
was attempting to flee.

509
00:22:13.062 --> 00:22:14.321
As we speak. he's being arraigned

510
00:22:14.422 --> 00:22:15.531
for the murder of Cecil Carbo.

511
00:22:15.598 --> 00:22:16.732
I expect he'll be remanded.

512
00:22:16.832 --> 00:22:17.832
Very good.

513
00:22:17.867 --> 00:22:19.268
And what about the crown?

514
00:22:19.301 --> 00:22:21.437
It wasn't in Mr. Salazar's possession

515
00:22:21.470 --> 00:22:23.239
when we took him into custody.

516
00:22:23.272 --> 00:22:25.408
So you have no idea where it is?

517
00:22:25.474 --> 00:22:27.276
Not yet.

518
00:22:27.309 --> 00:22:29.278
Mr. Salazar isn't cooperating with us.

519
00:22:29.378 --> 00:22:31.347
But we did find
evidence in his apartment

520
00:22:31.447 --> 00:22:32.882
that links him to the crime.

521
00:22:32.948 --> 00:22:34.784
We've been retracing his steps to see

522
00:22:34.850 --> 00:22:36.452
if we can figure out where
he might have hidden it.

523
00:22:36.485 --> 00:22:37.912
but so far. no luck.

524
00:22:37.978 --> 00:22:39.622
I have to tell you. the
Catholic community has

525
00:22:39.655 --> 00:22:41.724
been galvanized by this theft

526
00:22:41.791 --> 00:22:43.984
like nothing I can remember.

527
00:22:44.018 --> 00:22:47.354
It's essential that the crown be found.

528
00:22:47.455 --> 00:22:49.924
So what are you doing
to ensure its recovery?

529
00:22:49.990 --> 00:22:53.427
Respectfully. we're trying
to bring a killer to justice.

530
00:22:53.494 --> 00:22:57.339
So finding the relic is not our focus.

531
00:22:57.440 --> 00:22:58.808
It should be.

532
00:22:58.908 --> 00:23:01.477
You were the one that told me
the most important thing was

533
00:23:01.577 --> 00:23:03.679
getting justice for Cecil Carbo.

534
00:23:03.779 --> 00:23:07.141
And you think these things
are mutually exclusive?

535
00:23:07.208 --> 00:23:11.287
That crown was created
by ordinary people

536
00:23:11.353 --> 00:23:13.823
who then surrendered their treasure.

537
00:23:13.923 --> 00:23:15.257
their literal treasure.

538
00:23:15.291 --> 00:23:17.051
gold and stones that they pulled

539
00:23:17.151 --> 00:23:19.628
from the ground beneath their feet.

540
00:23:19.662 --> 00:23:22.131
So its creation. its beautiful story.

541
00:23:22.198 --> 00:23:25.292
it mirrors the gospel itself.

542
00:23:25.359 --> 00:23:26.794
I get it.

543
00:23:26.861 --> 00:23:28.204
And we're gonna do
everything we can to find it.

544
00:23:28.304 --> 00:23:29.705
You have my word.

545
00:23:29.738 --> 00:23:31.474
I don't want your word. Nick.

546
00:23:31.574 --> 00:23:34.176
I want your guarantee.

547
00:23:36.645 --> 00:23:39.582
Like I said. we'll do everything we can.

548
00:23:53.496 --> 00:23:54.563
Hey.

549
00:23:54.597 --> 00:23:56.098
Luis Salazar has been remanded.

550
00:23:56.198 --> 00:23:57.165
Good.

551
00:23:57.166 --> 00:23:58.400
How's our case?

552
00:23:58.501 --> 00:23:59.568
Solid.

553
00:23:59.668 --> 00:24:01.328
We don't have the murder weapon.

554
00:24:01.395 --> 00:24:04.039
But forensics has confirmed
that the circular glass cutter

555
00:24:04.140 --> 00:24:06.267
we found in Salazar's apartment is

556
00:24:06.333 --> 00:24:07.843
the same blade used to slice open

557
00:24:07.943 --> 00:24:09.612
the display case in the museum.

558
00:24:09.712 --> 00:24:11.981
And Salazar didn't just
have a plane ticket to Miami.

559
00:24:12.047 --> 00:24:14.542
He was connecting in Miami to Yemen.

560
00:24:14.608 --> 00:24:16.218
which doesn't have an extradition treaty

561
00:24:16.318 --> 00:24:17.553
with the United States.

562
00:24:17.653 --> 00:24:20.022
But the core of the case
is based on the testimony

563
00:24:20.122 --> 00:24:21.557
of the security guard. Joe Whitaker...

564
00:24:22.858 --> 00:24:24.894
And the Morse code
chatter between Salazar

565
00:24:24.994 --> 00:24:26.762
and his other accomplice.
Frank Stephens.

566
00:24:26.862 --> 00:24:29.023
Uh. about that.

567
00:24:29.089 --> 00:24:32.535
The defense is challenging
the admissibility of the pager.

568
00:24:32.601 --> 00:24:34.528
Your Honor. the detectives performed

569
00:24:34.595 --> 00:24:37.173
an illegal search of my
client's suitcase at JFK.

570
00:24:37.206 --> 00:24:39.808
There were clearly
exigent circumstances.

571
00:24:39.909 --> 00:24:41.468
The defendant was preparing

572
00:24:41.569 --> 00:24:44.071
to abscond to Yemen. carrying evidence

573
00:24:44.138 --> 00:24:45.748
that was vital to a
murder investigation.

574
00:24:45.781 --> 00:24:46.982
It doesn't matter.

575
00:24:47.082 --> 00:24:48.818
Mr. Salazar's suitcase
was gate-checked prior

576
00:24:48.884 --> 00:24:50.953
to the detectives' arrival.
which is a legal transfer

577
00:24:51.053 --> 00:24:52.087
of custody to the airline.

578
00:24:52.121 --> 00:24:53.255
Once that happens...

579
00:24:53.289 --> 00:24:54.949
Then you're saying. the suitcase was

580
00:24:54.982 --> 00:24:58.027
no longer in the immediate
control of Mr. Salazar.

581
00:24:58.093 --> 00:25:01.230
and therefore no longer
subject to a warrantless search.

582
00:25:01.297 --> 00:25:02.431
Correct.

583
00:25:02.464 --> 00:25:04.400
Your Honor. the inevitable
discovery doctrine

584
00:25:04.466 --> 00:25:06.302
speaks directly to this point.

585
00:25:06.402 --> 00:25:08.838
Federal authorities
were required by statute

586
00:25:08.904 --> 00:25:12.508
to inspect that bag once our
arrest triggered an alert.

587
00:25:12.608 --> 00:25:15.544
So the evidence... the pager...
would have been discovered

588
00:25:15.611 --> 00:25:17.279
inevitably. within minutes.

589
00:25:17.313 --> 00:25:18.772
Perhaps.

590
00:25:18.839 --> 00:25:21.283
But the inevitability doctrine
does not grant you the ability

591
00:25:21.383 --> 00:25:24.578
to retroactively justify
an improper search

592
00:25:24.645 --> 00:25:27.256
by conjuring up lawful versions

593
00:25:27.289 --> 00:25:29.225
of the events that never happened.

594
00:25:29.258 --> 00:25:32.228
Once that suitcase was
checked at the gate.

595
00:25:32.261 --> 00:25:34.830
it entered the exclusive custody

596
00:25:34.864 --> 00:25:37.967
of a federally regulated airline.

597
00:25:38.033 --> 00:25:43.622
The bag's contents are out.
which means the pager is out.

598
00:25:49.578 --> 00:25:52.147
Prior to February 18th.

599
00:25:52.248 --> 00:25:54.441
the day of Cecil Carbo's murder.

600
00:25:54.508 --> 00:25:56.552
did a man named Frank Stephens ask you

601
00:25:56.652 --> 00:25:58.854
to help him rob the museum?

602
00:25:58.954 --> 00:26:00.322
Yes.

603
00:26:00.356 --> 00:26:02.383
Frank and I were old friends.

604
00:26:02.483 --> 00:26:04.485
We grew up together.

605
00:26:04.551 --> 00:26:07.221
I had mentioned a few weeks before that

606
00:26:07.321 --> 00:26:09.223
that the crown was on display

607
00:26:09.323 --> 00:26:11.058
at the museum where I worked.

608
00:26:11.125 --> 00:26:12.559
Then. out of the blue. Frank asked

609
00:26:12.660 --> 00:26:14.169
how easy it would be to steal.

610
00:26:14.270 --> 00:26:15.904
I thought he was kidding.

611
00:26:15.971 --> 00:26:17.306
you know. joking around at first.

612
00:26:17.373 --> 00:26:20.676
But he told his buddy. Flaco.

613
00:26:20.776 --> 00:26:21.810
- because they...
- Sorry.

614
00:26:21.910 --> 00:26:24.413
By Flaco. you are referring to?

615
00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:26.048
Luis Salazar.

616
00:26:26.148 --> 00:26:27.750
He goes by Flaco.

617
00:26:27.850 --> 00:26:29.018
And you met Luis Salazar?

618
00:26:29.118 --> 00:26:30.986
Yes. two weeks before the heist.

619
00:26:31.086 --> 00:26:33.055
Frank and Salazar asked me to help them.

620
00:26:33.155 --> 00:26:34.390
said they would cut me in.

621
00:26:34.490 --> 00:26:37.693
Do you see Luis Salazar
in this courtroom?

622
00:26:37.793 --> 00:26:39.053
Right there.

623
00:26:39.086 --> 00:26:40.329
He's sitting right there.

624
00:26:40.396 --> 00:26:41.697
Your Honor. let the record reflect

625
00:26:41.797 --> 00:26:44.667
that the witness has identified
the defendant. Luis Salazar.

626
00:26:44.733 --> 00:26:46.260
The record shall so reflect.

627
00:26:46.327 --> 00:26:49.872
What help did you
provide in the robbery?

628
00:26:49.972 --> 00:26:53.767
I rebooted the museum CCTV
to turn the cameras off.

629
00:26:53.867 --> 00:26:57.871
smuggled out extra security
guard outfits and ID badges

630
00:26:57.938 --> 00:27:00.482
that I reported as lost
so Frank and Salazar could

631
00:27:00.549 --> 00:27:03.018
have access to the building.

632
00:27:03.052 --> 00:27:04.920
And on the morning of the murder.

633
00:27:05.020 --> 00:27:07.448
did you see the defendant?

634
00:27:07.548 --> 00:27:09.658
Yes. After I rebooted the cameras.

635
00:27:09.725 --> 00:27:10.784
I went upstairs to make sure

636
00:27:10.851 --> 00:27:12.386
Frank and Salazar got inside okay.

637
00:27:12.453 --> 00:27:14.029
They were there. so I
went back downstairs.

638
00:27:14.096 --> 00:27:15.464
Thank you. Nothing further.

639
00:27:18.033 --> 00:27:20.769
Mr. Whitaker. you testified earlier that

640
00:27:20.869 --> 00:27:22.471
the police threatened to...

641
00:27:22.538 --> 00:27:23.797
to charge you with felony murder

642
00:27:23.864 --> 00:27:25.232
if you didn't testify today.

643
00:27:25.299 --> 00:27:28.043
Yes. I cut a deal for reduced charges.

644
00:27:28.077 --> 00:27:30.946
So you're a criminal.
a criminal who swore

645
00:27:31.046 --> 00:27:32.748
to defend the Atlas Museum of Art

646
00:27:32.815 --> 00:27:33.982
and robbed it instead.

647
00:27:34.049 --> 00:27:35.751
And now. to avoid responsibility.

648
00:27:35.784 --> 00:27:37.319
you've agreed to lie in court.

649
00:27:37.419 --> 00:27:38.645
- Objection.
- Sustained.

650
00:27:38.746 --> 00:27:40.322
Watch it. Mr. Wood.

651
00:27:42.216 --> 00:27:43.792
How tall are you. Mr. Whitaker?

652
00:27:43.892 --> 00:27:45.828
I'm about 5'7".

653
00:27:45.894 --> 00:27:47.963
Did you tell the police
that the defendant

654
00:27:47.996 --> 00:27:49.590
was about your height?

655
00:27:49.656 --> 00:27:51.225
Yeah. I... I...

656
00:27:51.291 --> 00:27:52.735
- I think so.
- I'm confused.

657
00:27:52.801 --> 00:27:55.037
Mr. Salazar is 6'1".

658
00:27:55.104 --> 00:27:56.205
Okay.

659
00:27:56.238 --> 00:27:58.140
You didn't actually witness the shooting

660
00:27:58.173 --> 00:28:00.509
of Cecil Carbo. did you?

661
00:28:00.609 --> 00:28:02.436
- No.
- And when you allegedly saw

662
00:28:02.503 --> 00:28:04.338
Mr. Salazar inside the museum on the day

663
00:28:04.438 --> 00:28:08.817
of Mr. Carbo's death.
you're sure it was him?

664
00:28:08.851 --> 00:28:09.851
Uh. yeah.

665
00:28:09.852 --> 00:28:11.687
Because the prosecutors seem to think

666
00:28:11.787 --> 00:28:13.522
that the men who did
this were wearing masks.

667
00:28:13.622 --> 00:28:14.589
He was.

668
00:28:14.590 --> 00:28:16.258
Then how did you recognize him?

669
00:28:16.291 --> 00:28:17.351
I don't know. Because...

670
00:28:17.451 --> 00:28:18.527
You don't know. or this wasn't part

671
00:28:18.627 --> 00:28:20.020
of the dress rehearsal with the DA?

672
00:28:20.087 --> 00:28:21.864
- Objection.
- Sustained.

673
00:28:21.964 --> 00:28:23.599
Look. I went up there and
I looked him in the eyes.

674
00:28:23.665 --> 00:28:25.267
and he nodded. just like we planned.

675
00:28:25.367 --> 00:28:26.635
It was him.

676
00:28:26.735 --> 00:28:28.203
And I remember
everything about it. okay?

677
00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:30.439
We were standing under an
Exit sign outside the room

678
00:28:30.506 --> 00:28:31.840
where the crown was.

679
00:28:31.940 --> 00:28:34.209
I remember there was a
dude on crutches next to us.

680
00:28:34.309 --> 00:28:35.869
I remember I was worried he was gonna

681
00:28:35.969 --> 00:28:38.147
take forever to get out of
there once the heist started.

682
00:28:38.213 --> 00:28:42.284
I... I... I saw the ID
badge Salazar had on.

683
00:28:42.317 --> 00:28:44.878
my old badge that I
reported as lost. okay?

684
00:28:44.945 --> 00:28:46.713
I remember it all!

685
00:28:46.814 --> 00:28:48.891
Okay? I'm not lying.

686
00:28:56.231 --> 00:28:57.900
That wasn't super fun.

687
00:28:58.000 --> 00:28:59.326
Agreed.

688
00:28:59.393 --> 00:29:01.895
Our star witness got
beat up pretty good.

689
00:29:01.995 --> 00:29:03.739
Well. he did mention
something new. though...

690
00:29:03.839 --> 00:29:05.074
a guy on crutches.

691
00:29:05.140 --> 00:29:07.176
a museum patron that
was on the second floor

692
00:29:07.276 --> 00:29:09.678
while the shooting and robbery unfolded.

693
00:29:09.711 --> 00:29:11.747
It's possible that if
he was having a hard time

694
00:29:11.847 --> 00:29:14.141
- leaving the building...
- He could be a witness?

695
00:29:14.208 --> 00:29:15.476
Something.

696
00:29:15.542 --> 00:29:17.010
We've taken a few hits on this one.

697
00:29:17.077 --> 00:29:18.378
It'd be great to claw some of that back.

698
00:29:19.555 --> 00:29:21.582
That's a good idea.

699
00:29:21.682 --> 00:29:24.193
Cameras inside the museum were down.

700
00:29:24.293 --> 00:29:26.653
but ask the detectives to
review exterior footage.

701
00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:30.390
See if they can find a man on
crutches leaving the museum.

702
00:29:33.669 --> 00:29:36.538
Yeah. I fell off a stupid ladder.

703
00:29:36.572 --> 00:29:39.308
busted my calcaneus.

704
00:29:39.374 --> 00:29:41.101
I never heard of it either...

705
00:29:41.201 --> 00:29:42.778
heel bone.

706
00:29:42.845 --> 00:29:44.505
Still can't put any weight on it.

707
00:29:44.571 --> 00:29:45.981
Such a drag.

708
00:29:47.483 --> 00:29:49.051
How did you even find me?

709
00:29:49.118 --> 00:29:51.386
You were the only one
who fled the art museum

710
00:29:51.487 --> 00:29:53.155
that morning on crutches.

711
00:29:53.188 --> 00:29:56.191
Our detectives found security
footage from across the street.

712
00:29:56.258 --> 00:29:58.160
and you popped in facial recognition.

713
00:29:58.227 --> 00:29:59.795
You're not in any trouble.

714
00:29:59.862 --> 00:30:01.964
To the contrary. we need your help.

715
00:30:02.030 --> 00:30:04.224
Is it true you were there that morning?

716
00:30:04.291 --> 00:30:06.835
Yeah. I went to see the crown.

717
00:30:06.902 --> 00:30:08.770
I drop by once a week or so.

718
00:30:08.804 --> 00:30:10.205
That thing's a big deal.

719
00:30:10.305 --> 00:30:11.765
Were you close enough to the robbery

720
00:30:11.798 --> 00:30:13.575
- to see what transpired?
- No.

721
00:30:13.675 --> 00:30:15.869
But I heard everything.

722
00:30:15.936 --> 00:30:17.579
Walk us through it.

723
00:30:17.679 --> 00:30:19.640
Well. the thieves walked around first.

724
00:30:19.740 --> 00:30:21.116
making some big announcements.

725
00:30:21.216 --> 00:30:22.618
Said there was some
sort of private event.

726
00:30:22.651 --> 00:30:24.144
Right. to clear out the area.

727
00:30:24.244 --> 00:30:25.387
Exactly.

728
00:30:25.454 --> 00:30:26.955
And I'm such a slow-poke these days.

729
00:30:27.055 --> 00:30:29.057
it was taking me forever
to get out of there.

730
00:30:29.124 --> 00:30:31.585
I saw the guy that died run in there.

731
00:30:31.652 --> 00:30:33.228
And then I hear them all start screaming

732
00:30:33.262 --> 00:30:36.265
at each other. and then bang. bang!

733
00:30:36.365 --> 00:30:37.599
I was terrified.

734
00:30:37.666 --> 00:30:39.601
I just got behind the
nearest thing I could find.

735
00:30:39.668 --> 00:30:41.770
some sculpture. to kind of ride it out

736
00:30:41.870 --> 00:30:43.539
till the coast was clear.

737
00:30:43.605 --> 00:30:45.674
What else could you hear?

738
00:30:45.741 --> 00:30:46.975
The bad guys?

739
00:30:47.075 --> 00:30:48.477
They were pissed.

740
00:30:48.577 --> 00:30:51.146
Didn't sound like this was part
of the plan. killing anybody.

741
00:30:51.180 --> 00:30:53.674
One guy goes. "Damn it."

742
00:30:53.740 --> 00:30:57.119
The other guy goes.
"Leonard better deliver."

743
00:31:04.893 --> 00:31:06.795
You know. to this
day. my mom yells at me

744
00:31:06.828 --> 00:31:08.530
if I don't pray before I eat?

745
00:31:09.998 --> 00:31:11.667
I never understood the point.

746
00:31:11.700 --> 00:31:14.528
It's like talking on the phone.

747
00:31:14.595 --> 00:31:17.372
and there's nobody on the other end.

748
00:31:17.472 --> 00:31:19.374
But do me a favor?

749
00:31:19.474 --> 00:31:22.878
Pray that we figure
out who this Leonard is.

750
00:31:22.945 --> 00:31:25.981
I think your prayers have been answered.

751
00:31:26.014 --> 00:31:28.584
Got a hit in the ATU database.

752
00:31:28.617 --> 00:31:31.486
an import-export guy in Canarsie.

753
00:31:31.587 --> 00:31:33.155
Leonard Hawkins.

754
00:31:33.255 --> 00:31:35.390
A lot of guys named Leonard out there.

755
00:31:35.457 --> 00:31:39.061
For sure. but this
guy is Salazar's uncle.

756
00:31:48.687 --> 00:31:51.331
Mr. Hawkins. do you own a business?

757
00:31:51.398 --> 00:31:54.576
Yes. I am the president
and sole employee

758
00:31:54.643 --> 00:31:57.746
of an LLC called MTH Import-Export.

759
00:31:57.846 --> 00:32:00.649
I sell items and buy items...

760
00:32:00.682 --> 00:32:03.185
art. watches. jewelry. you name it.

761
00:32:03.285 --> 00:32:05.621
Sounds like a pawnshop?

762
00:32:05.687 --> 00:32:07.923
I prefer import-export. thank you.

763
00:32:07.990 --> 00:32:09.625
So do my clients.

764
00:32:09.658 --> 00:32:12.260
My business requires a
certain amount of discretion.

765
00:32:12.361 --> 00:32:14.496
And the defendant. Luis Salazar.

766
00:32:14.529 --> 00:32:16.531
is it true that he is your nephew?

767
00:32:16.632 --> 00:32:18.467
Yeah. kind of.

768
00:32:18.533 --> 00:32:20.102
Can you explain that for the jury?

769
00:32:20.202 --> 00:32:22.838
Well. he's my nephew by marriage.

770
00:32:22.871 --> 00:32:25.774
except I'm not married
to the family anymore.

771
00:32:25.841 --> 00:32:29.177
For 12 years. I was married
to his mother's sister.

772
00:32:29.211 --> 00:32:31.546
We don't talk much... ever. really.

773
00:32:31.647 --> 00:32:35.042
I always thought he was
kind of a screw-up. honestly.

774
00:32:35.108 --> 00:32:37.686
And yet. did Mr. Salazar have occasion

775
00:32:37.786 --> 00:32:40.722
to call you just prior to February 18th.

776
00:32:40.822 --> 00:32:42.891
the day of Cecil Carbo's murder?

777
00:32:42.991 --> 00:32:44.092
Yes. he did.

778
00:32:44.192 --> 00:32:45.394
That was four days before.

779
00:32:45.494 --> 00:32:46.995
To say what?

780
00:32:47.029 --> 00:32:50.232
He asked if I could move
an expensive piece of art.

781
00:32:50.332 --> 00:32:53.068
Did he mention what it might be?

782
00:32:53.101 --> 00:32:54.569
Hell no.

783
00:32:54.603 --> 00:32:56.304
I mean. if I'd had known.
I would have told him

784
00:32:56.371 --> 00:32:57.773
he was insane. which he clearly...

785
00:32:57.806 --> 00:32:59.274
Objection. Your Honor.

786
00:32:59.308 --> 00:33:00.967
Sustained.

787
00:33:01.068 --> 00:33:03.245
All he told me was that
it wasn't a painting.

788
00:33:03.345 --> 00:33:06.248
It was more like jewels.
gold and emeralds.

789
00:33:06.348 --> 00:33:09.618
Did the defendant contact you
after the day of the theft?

790
00:33:09.718 --> 00:33:10.877
Yes.

791
00:33:10.944 --> 00:33:12.387
And what did he say?

792
00:33:12.454 --> 00:33:14.581
He said that he...

793
00:33:14.648 --> 00:33:16.458
that the thing that he was going to do.

794
00:33:16.491 --> 00:33:17.993
that he actually did it.

795
00:33:18.060 --> 00:33:20.662
And what did you interpret that to mean?

796
00:33:20.729 --> 00:33:23.965
That he stole the thing
that he was going to steal.

797
00:33:23.999 --> 00:33:24.999
Thank you.

798
00:33:25.033 --> 00:33:26.435
Nothing further.

799
00:33:39.047 --> 00:33:40.047
Mr. Baxter?

800
00:33:40.115 --> 00:33:41.917
Mr. Wood is here to see you.

801
00:33:42.017 --> 00:33:44.486
Luis Salazar's defense lawyer to see me?

802
00:33:44.586 --> 00:33:45.645
He's not alone.

803
00:33:45.679 --> 00:33:48.023
He's with the Archbishop.

804
00:33:48.123 --> 00:33:49.123
Okay.

805
00:33:49.191 --> 00:33:50.525
Send him in.

806
00:33:54.830 --> 00:33:56.832
Gentlemen.

807
00:33:56.932 --> 00:33:58.834
Thank you for seeing us.

808
00:33:58.867 --> 00:34:01.103
Please. have a seat.

809
00:34:01.169 --> 00:34:03.672
I wasn't aware the two
of you knew each other.

810
00:34:03.772 --> 00:34:05.674
Mr. Wood and I have been in conversation

811
00:34:05.774 --> 00:34:07.768
about our mutual interest.

812
00:34:07.834 --> 00:34:09.211
Which is?

813
00:34:10.746 --> 00:34:13.940
The Crown of Popayán.

814
00:34:14.007 --> 00:34:16.543
Anything concerning the Salazar case.

815
00:34:16.643 --> 00:34:18.812
you should be talking
to Nolan Price. not me.

816
00:34:18.879 --> 00:34:21.623
We felt that this should
involve the full weight

817
00:34:21.690 --> 00:34:24.426
of your office... you.

818
00:34:24.493 --> 00:34:26.261
We'd like to discuss a plea.

819
00:34:26.328 --> 00:34:29.564
From what I understand. the
case is pretty much over.

820
00:34:29.631 --> 00:34:32.067
Why would we possibly
consider a plea now?

821
00:34:32.134 --> 00:34:35.470
We're prepared to have
the crown returned.

822
00:34:35.537 --> 00:34:37.906
That doesn't sound like
it involves me at all.

823
00:34:40.700 --> 00:34:42.544
There's a price tag.

824
00:34:42.644 --> 00:34:44.012
Huh.

825
00:34:44.045 --> 00:34:47.149
And I don't suppose you'd
consider doing the right thing.

826
00:34:47.249 --> 00:34:48.917
just because it's the right thing to do.

827
00:34:49.017 --> 00:34:50.752
I know that's asking a lot.

828
00:34:53.822 --> 00:34:57.676
Mr. Wood. could you give
us a moment alone. please?

829
00:35:05.667 --> 00:35:10.030
Nick. I feel like over
the years. you and I.

830
00:35:10.096 --> 00:35:12.874
we got a fair read on each other. right?

831
00:35:12.974 --> 00:35:14.601
I think so.

832
00:35:14.701 --> 00:35:15.936
So then I can tell you this

833
00:35:16.002 --> 00:35:17.379
without it feeling like an attack.

834
00:35:17.412 --> 00:35:20.182
It's not. It's an observation.

835
00:35:20.282 --> 00:35:22.717
You're not an overtly religious person.

836
00:35:22.818 --> 00:35:25.537
devout. like your father.

837
00:35:26.888 --> 00:35:31.785
I have my own beliefs. but
yeah. that's probably true.

838
00:35:31.852 --> 00:35:33.453
But you are a student of history

839
00:35:33.553 --> 00:35:35.956
and someone who could
appreciate perspectives

840
00:35:36.022 --> 00:35:38.366
that might not be your own.

841
00:35:38.466 --> 00:35:39.901
Thank you. I think.

842
00:35:39.935 --> 00:35:41.736
I'd like to think that's true.

843
00:35:41.837 --> 00:35:43.271
Here's one.

844
00:35:43.305 --> 00:35:46.241
I would encourage you not to
think of the Crown of Popayán

845
00:35:46.341 --> 00:35:48.810
as an object.

846
00:35:48.910 --> 00:35:50.145
Okay.

847
00:35:51.546 --> 00:35:53.081
Tell me.

848
00:35:53.148 --> 00:35:57.143
The Crown of Popayán is proof

849
00:35:57.244 --> 00:36:00.655
right here on Earth of God's grace.

850
00:36:00.722 --> 00:36:03.158
It draws us closer to God.

851
00:36:03.225 --> 00:36:05.894
Millions of people believe that.

852
00:36:05.927 --> 00:36:08.722
That sounds lovely. comforting.

853
00:36:08.788 --> 00:36:11.166
I mean that.

854
00:36:11.233 --> 00:36:14.269
Many of them are right here
in New York. your constituents.

855
00:36:14.369 --> 00:36:18.340
the people whose interest
you were elected to serve.

856
00:36:20.575 --> 00:36:25.080
To refuse this offer would mean
sacrificing the spiritual good

857
00:36:25.146 --> 00:36:28.975
of the faithful for the
emotional satisfaction

858
00:36:29.009 --> 00:36:30.685
of punishment.

859
00:36:36.958 --> 00:36:39.361
Mercy is not weakness. Nick.

860
00:36:40.795 --> 00:36:42.364
Please.

861
00:36:55.010 --> 00:36:56.770
We're doing what?

862
00:36:56.836 --> 00:36:59.481
In exchange for reducing
charges and advocating

863
00:36:59.514 --> 00:37:02.884
for a lenient sentence.
Luis Salazar will reveal

864
00:37:02.951 --> 00:37:04.377
the location of the crown.

865
00:37:04.477 --> 00:37:06.279
No. I understood the offer.

866
00:37:06.346 --> 00:37:09.149
I don't understand why
we're even considering it.

867
00:37:09.215 --> 00:37:12.719
This is nothing but an act of
desperation at the 11th hour.

868
00:37:12.819 --> 00:37:15.230
We have Luis Salazar dead to rights.

869
00:37:15.297 --> 00:37:18.400
I'm confident the jury
will return a guilty verdict

870
00:37:18.466 --> 00:37:19.901
tomorrow morning.

871
00:37:20.001 --> 00:37:21.503
I'm not sure that's
the math on this one.

872
00:37:21.536 --> 00:37:24.205
No. it's the only math that matters.

873
00:37:24.306 --> 00:37:26.741
We are holding a man
to account for murder.

874
00:37:26.808 --> 00:37:28.777
And this thing?

875
00:37:28.843 --> 00:37:30.145
It's just a thing.

876
00:37:30.245 --> 00:37:32.238
It's immaterial. Nick.

877
00:37:32.339 --> 00:37:34.249
This isn't a debate. Nolan.

878
00:37:34.316 --> 00:37:38.353
Prosecutorial discretion exists
precisely for cases like this.

879
00:37:38.453 --> 00:37:40.355
We're not here to solely satisfy

880
00:37:40.388 --> 00:37:42.090
a lust for maximum punishment.

881
00:37:42.157 --> 00:37:43.858
We're here to protect
the public interest.

882
00:37:43.959 --> 00:37:48.355
which. in this case. is more
complicated than a prison term.

883
00:37:48.421 --> 00:37:50.198
It doesn't matter that I don't believe

884
00:37:50.298 --> 00:37:51.533
what you're saying. Nick.

885
00:37:51.566 --> 00:37:54.235
I don't think you do. either.

886
00:37:54.269 --> 00:37:56.037
Oh. right.

887
00:37:56.071 --> 00:37:58.206
I keep forgetting how
you really feel about me.

888
00:37:58.306 --> 00:37:59.866
Come on. Nick.

889
00:37:59.933 --> 00:38:01.843
Let's at least be honest about
why this is really happening.

890
00:38:01.910 --> 00:38:04.713
There are 2 1/2 million
Catholics in New York.

891
00:38:04.746 --> 00:38:06.047
They vote.

892
00:38:06.081 --> 00:38:07.415
That is why this is happening.

893
00:38:07.515 --> 00:38:08.850
You're wrong.

894
00:38:08.917 --> 00:38:10.352
If we drop this to murder two

895
00:38:10.452 --> 00:38:12.354
and recommend the low-end
of the sentencing range

896
00:38:12.420 --> 00:38:14.589
and bring the crown home in one piece.

897
00:38:14.622 --> 00:38:16.925
that is a win for the many. many people

898
00:38:17.025 --> 00:38:18.393
who believe in this thing.

899
00:38:18.426 --> 00:38:20.295
That means it's a win
for the City of New York.

900
00:38:20.362 --> 00:38:22.230
And that means it's a win for us.

901
00:38:22.263 --> 00:38:23.957
For God's sake. there's an argument

902
00:38:24.024 --> 00:38:25.934
to be made the crown doesn't
even belong to the church.

903
00:38:26.034 --> 00:38:27.469
That is not our concern.

904
00:38:27.535 --> 00:38:29.195
Right. right.

905
00:38:29.262 --> 00:38:31.573
Not a lot of Indigenous
Colombians around here.

906
00:38:31.640 --> 00:38:32.640
I'm done.

907
00:38:32.674 --> 00:38:35.377
Make the deal.

908
00:38:42.584 --> 00:38:45.979
Today is not about what was lost.

909
00:38:46.079 --> 00:38:49.315
Today is about what was found.

910
00:38:49.416 --> 00:38:53.061
about the resilience of faith.

911
00:38:53.161 --> 00:38:55.230
What happened here caused so much pain.

912
00:38:55.330 --> 00:38:57.332
confusion. even anger.

913
00:38:57.432 --> 00:39:01.169
But I would argue that
we are better for it.

914
00:39:01.269 --> 00:39:02.269
Gold will tarnish.

915
00:39:02.303 --> 00:39:05.173
Emeralds will crumble to dust.

916
00:39:05.240 --> 00:39:09.678
But what the Crown of
Popayán proclaims is eternal.

917
00:39:09.744 --> 00:39:12.347
Gratitude is stronger than greed.

918
00:39:12.447 --> 00:39:15.984
and God does not abandon his people.

919
00:39:16.017 --> 00:39:19.179
And finally. I would like
to thank Nicholas Baxter.

920
00:39:19.279 --> 00:39:22.515
our esteemed district attorney.
for making this happen.

921
00:39:22.582 --> 00:39:24.259
Thank you. Your Eminence.

922
00:39:31.066 --> 00:39:33.301
Not a mention of Cecil.

923
00:39:33.401 --> 00:39:34.869
Not one word.

924
00:39:34.969 --> 00:39:36.404
Mrs. Carbo. I know that...

925
00:39:36.471 --> 00:39:38.832
You people promised us
that you'd do everything

926
00:39:38.865 --> 00:39:40.375
to get justice for Cecil.

927
00:39:40.442 --> 00:39:42.377
The man who did this has pleaded guilty.

928
00:39:42.477 --> 00:39:44.204
He's going to prison for 15 years.

929
00:39:44.304 --> 00:39:46.047
So he'll be out before he turns 40.

930
00:39:46.147 --> 00:39:48.550
Why does he get a life.
but my dad doesn't?

931
00:39:51.820 --> 00:39:57.125
As prosecutors. we are
not here just to satisfy

932
00:39:57.225 --> 00:39:58.893
a lust for punishment.

933
00:39:58.993 --> 00:40:02.163
We also have to protect
the public interest.

934
00:40:02.230 --> 00:40:03.898
which. in this case...

935
00:40:06.367 --> 00:40:09.070
It got complicated.

936
00:40:14.075 --> 00:40:15.376
Can you even believe

937
00:40:15.477 --> 00:40:18.246
the words coming out of your mouth?

938
00:40:20.982 --> 00:40:22.350
Come on.

939
00:41:12.718 --> 00:41:17.718
